    "recap_headline": "Rutgers University",
    "recap_text": "PISCATAWAY, N.J. \u2013\nRutgers baseball dropped game two of its series against Michigan State by a score of 9-3 on Saturday\u00a0at Bainton Field.\nThe Scarlet Knights (10-8, 1-1) fell behind 8-0 early and were unable to rally against\u00a0the Spartans (5-12, 1-4), who forced a rubber match Sunday afternoon.\nMSU collected nine extra base-hits on the day, using four home runs, four doubles and a triple to slug its way to a victory. A solo homer in the second made it 1-0 before a triple, single and sac fly made it 5-0 in the third. Two more homers in fourth pushed the advantage to 8-0.\nBack-to-back doubles from\nRyan Jaros\nand\nQuinten Perilli\nin the fifth got RU on the board. The Spartans responded with a solo homer in the seventh to make it 9-1. While a\nPeyton Bonds\ndouble and\nJoey Erace\nsingle each scored a run in the seventh, it was too little, too late as MSU finished off the 9-3 victory.\nOffensively,\nTrey Wells\n,\nMatt Chatelle\n,\nRyan Jaros\n,\nQuinten Perilli\nand\nJoey Erace\neach collected two hits.\nJordan Savi\u00f1on (1.1),\nMatthew Cruz\n(0.2),\nFinn Haines\n(0.2) and\nTyler Kane\n(0.2) all contributed scoreless outings of relief.\nThe rubber game between Rutgers and Michigan State is set for Sunday, with first pitch set for 1 p.m. at Bainton Field.\nFollow Rutgers Baseball on Social Media\nX\n|\nInstagram\n|\nFacebook"
